commit.message:
Keep python2 compatability

Was broken by "Add additional error to lockfile function"
Add readme entry for new display parameter

Add possibility to define display to start with

Just pass display as kwarg to the constructor.

Add additional error to lockfile function

It seems when an actual Xvfb is running the locking failes with an
Permnission error when opening the file, not only with the currently
expected one.
Reproduce via starting an actual instance:
$ Xvfb :11
And then try to open the file, e.g.:
$ echo test > /tmp/.X11-lock
bash: /tmp/.X11-lock: Permission denied
Refactor display lock into own function
